<!--BOX MODEL IN CSS: styling related properties INSITED BOX
BORDER:outline for every content
box-shadow:l-r,t-b,blur,color

border-style:(dashed,solid,dotted)
syn:border-style:dashed,double,solid;
U6
border-width:thin,thick,large,small,medium
border-width:medium;
1st way: border-width:1px              top right bottom left
2nd way: border-width:2px 10px         2px(t,b) 10px(r,l)
3rd way:border-width:2px 3px 8px 15px  2(t) 3(r) 8(b) 15(l)

border-color:rgba(255)
border-color:rgba(56,67,223,1);

border-radius:convert box into curve
border-radius:25px;

border(shorthand property)-written in single line


MARGIN:gives gap between 2 r more elements
margin-left:%
margin-right:%
top,bottom
if u want to center:margin-top;margin-left(adjusting four sides)

PADDING:gives gap between content inside the box(spacing in box)
padding-top:%
bottom
left
right


-->
